&lt;p&gt;Staff Nurse, Band 5&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for &lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt; nurses to join our In-patient unit at Meadowview Intermediate care unit , Queen Mary&#39;s Hospital in Sidcup Kent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our intermediate care Unit is a multi-disciplinary integrated team that provides short stay rehabilitation to service users and a comprehensive assessment service to identify goals and integrated care management plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated and skilled registered nurses with excellent communication skills and basic nursing care to join our team. The skills that you may expect to have include: catheterisation, wound care, cannulation, phlebotomy, IVs etc (Training will also be provided).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome applications from newly qualified nurses with a drive to build on their pre-registration experience and knowledge to ensure that they deliver high standard of care to service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Oxleas operates a probationary period, further information is available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandra Hungwe Unit Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sandra.Hungwe@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;02039 107115&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
